#: ../../H/hardcoded.rst:5
msgid "hardcoded"
msgstr "hardcoded"

#: ../../H/hardcoded.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../H/hardcoded.rst:10
msgid ""
"[common] Said of data inserted directly into a program, where it cannot be "
"easily modified, as opposed to data in some :ref:`profile`\\, resource (see "
":ref:`de-rezz` sense 2), or environment variable that a :ref:`user` or "
"hacker can easily modify."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]\\ :ref:`user`\\ やハッカーが容易に変更できる\\ :ref:`profile`\\ 、リソース(\\ :ref:`de-"
"rezz`\\ 語義2を参照)、環境変数の中のデータとは対照的に、容易には変更できないようにプログラムに直接挿入されたデータについて言う。"

#: ../../H/hardcoded.rst:13
msgid ""
"In C, this is esp. applied to use of a literal instead of a :code:`#define` "
"macro (see :ref:`magic-number`\\)."
msgstr ""
"Cでは、これは特に\\ :code:`#define`\\ マクロの代わりにリテラルを使うことに適用される(\\ :ref:`magic-"
"number`\\ を参照)。"
